1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:40,640
[You are My Fateful Love]
[EP06]

3
00:02:55,039 --> 00:02:56,960
I think we have to talk about

4
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:58,039
the performance.

5
00:02:58,599 --> 00:02:59,759
Yeah, I think it's a good idea

6
00:02:59,759 --> 00:03:00,879
to talk about it.

7
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:02,840
So what ideas have you got?

8
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:09,360
[Honey?]

9
00:03:10,159 --> 00:03:11,280
[Are you... Are you home?]

10
00:03:16,439 --> 00:03:17,039
Ruan Yu?

11
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,680
Yeah, yeah, I'm almost home.

12
00:03:19,319 --> 00:03:19,840
[Okay.]

13
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,439
[You're picking me up at the crossroads?]

14
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:26,680
[Alright.]

15
00:03:28,439 --> 00:03:29,680
[I'll be there in five minutes.]

16
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,000
[Are you being followed?]

17
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,000
Stay calm.

18
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:38,919
Head to where there are people and lights.

19
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:40,240
[Tell him]

20
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,400
[I'm on my way to you right now.]

21
00:03:41,599 --> 00:03:42,919
I'm already heading your way.

22
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:46,520
I'm almost there.

23
00:03:51,039 --> 00:03:51,639
Uh,

24
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,159
it's okay now, Mr. Xu.
I'm home.

25
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:57,520
[I guess I just overreacted.]

26
00:04:00,599 --> 00:04:01,319
Glad you're safe.

27
00:04:02,039 --> 00:04:02,960
Get some rest.

28
00:04:03,719 --> 00:04:05,039
I'm already dealing with

29
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:06,680
those posts online.

30
00:04:09,319 --> 00:04:09,879
Honey?

31
00:04:10,719 --> 00:04:11,719
Are you... Are you home?

32
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:13,639
Well,

33
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:14,960
I'm so sorry.

34
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:16,160
I meant to

35
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:17,480
call a friend just now,

36
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:19,439
but I dialed your number by mistake.

37
00:04:34,399 --> 00:04:35,120
What's wrong?

38
00:04:35,959 --> 00:04:36,920
Mr. Xu,

39
00:04:37,639 --> 00:04:38,079
there's

40
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:39,480
a black van

41
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:41,360
parked downstairs.

42
00:04:42,079 --> 00:04:43,279
[It wasn't there]

43
00:04:43,279 --> 00:04:44,040
[when I just got here.]

44
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:45,959
Can you make out the license plate?

45
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:48,920
Not really,

46
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,160
but it looks like

47
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:52,360
the kind of van used for abductions.

48
00:04:58,319 --> 00:04:59,560
It's probably not

49
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:00,839
what you're worried about.

50
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:01,959
Even if it is,

51
00:05:01,959 --> 00:05:03,319
they won't just break in.

52
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,439
I need you to do two things right now:

53
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:06,199
First,

54
00:05:06,519 --> 00:05:07,319
send me your location

55
00:05:07,519 --> 00:05:08,920
and your property management

56
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:10,079
or security office's number.

57
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,319
Second, grab your phone

58
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,439
and check the peephole.

59
00:05:14,639 --> 00:05:15,120
Okay.

60
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,160
Done.

61
00:05:29,879 --> 00:05:30,600
Stay quiet first.

62
00:05:32,079 --> 00:05:33,600
[If you see someone suspicious]

63
00:05:33,759 --> 00:05:34,160
[and they]

64
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:35,199
haven't made a move,

65
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,720
don't lock the door yet.

66
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,959
Step back away from the door,

67
00:05:39,319 --> 00:05:40,120
turn on speakerphone,

68
00:05:40,279 --> 00:05:41,319
and call my name loudly.

69
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,879
Say you're doing laundry

70
00:05:43,279 --> 00:05:43,959
and tell me to get the door.

71
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:45,160
Understand?

72
00:05:46,399 --> 00:05:46,920
Understood.

73
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:49,000
If they don't leave

74
00:05:49,399 --> 00:05:50,560
after you do that,

75
00:05:51,279 --> 00:05:52,399
lock the door immediately

76
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:53,800
and call the police.

77
00:06:05,879 --> 00:06:06,439
What's wrong?

78
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:10,639
Hello?

79
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:17,560
[Sorry,]

80
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,079
[the number you've dialed is powered off.]

81
00:06:20,959 --> 00:06:22,439
Ruan Yu? You home?

82
00:06:40,279 --> 00:06:41,519
It's me, Li Shican.

83
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,199
Shican?
What are you doing here?

84
00:06:47,199 --> 00:06:48,120
Didn't we agree

85
00:06:48,279 --> 00:06:49,439
to meet at our usual spot?

86
00:06:50,879 --> 00:06:51,800
I thought you called me
about your livestream?

87
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:54,839
You watched my livestream?

88
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:57,639
Mingying and I were bored
at home the other day,

89
00:06:58,279 --> 00:06:59,360
so we caught your stream.

90
00:07:01,079 --> 00:07:02,480
You two really cared about me.

91
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:05,240
Can I come in?

92
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:06,720
I'm kind of worried...

93
00:07:07,199 --> 00:07:08,240
Yeah, of course, come in.

94
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:15,360
Shican,

95
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:16,920
I don't have men's slippers here.

96
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:18,120
Just keep your shoes on.

97
00:07:23,399 --> 00:07:24,319
Still no boyfriend?

98
00:07:26,319 --> 00:07:27,360
You weren't this gossipy

99
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:28,199
before you entered show business.

100
00:07:32,399 --> 00:07:32,879
Have a seat.

101
00:07:33,519 --> 00:07:34,000
Alright.

102
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:39,600
Uh...

103
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:41,240
It's fine, really.

104
00:07:49,319 --> 00:07:50,199
I tune out

105
00:07:50,199 --> 00:07:51,800
everyone else's gossip,

106
00:07:52,199 --> 00:07:52,879
but not yours.

107
00:07:53,759 --> 00:07:54,959
You're my...

108
00:07:57,759 --> 00:07:58,439
most trusted senior.

109
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,560
So you do remember I'm your senior.

110
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,319
Couldn't even call me that earlier.

111
00:08:04,279 --> 00:08:04,839
My bad.

112
00:08:05,319 --> 00:08:06,959
This is my apology gift.

113
00:08:10,079 --> 00:08:11,680
I passed by the shop on the way,

114
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,079
so I grabbed one for you.

115
00:08:13,839 --> 00:08:14,879
Wait, this is the milk tea shop

116
00:08:14,879 --> 00:08:15,839
from the university town!

117
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:17,319
It's still open?

118
00:08:20,439 --> 00:08:20,920
Here.
Thanks.

119
00:08:24,759 --> 00:08:25,720
Double bean milk tea,

120
00:08:26,199 --> 00:08:27,319
full sugar, no tea base.

121
00:08:27,879 --> 00:08:28,800
Swapped cow's milk for soy milk,

122
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:30,600
red beans only, no mung beans.

123
00:08:34,279 --> 00:08:36,519
I still have the memo from

124
00:08:36,519 --> 00:08:37,279
when I ran errands for seniors
back in the day,

125
00:08:38,399 --> 00:08:39,519
just without the names attached.

126
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:41,720
Lucky I got it right, otherwise

127
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,879
I'd be making things even worse.

128
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:45,759
That's so thoughtful of you.

129
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,000
I don't have much
to offer here,

130
00:08:49,519 --> 00:08:50,559
let me get you a glass of warm water.

131
00:08:51,639 --> 00:08:52,799
Sure, warm water is perfect.

132
00:08:53,279 --> 00:08:54,600
I'm resting my voice these days,

133
00:08:54,679 --> 00:08:55,240
so I'm laying off sugary drinks.

134
00:08:55,279 --> 00:08:56,639
Alright, one second.

135
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:06,320
Here you go.

136
00:09:07,559 --> 00:09:07,960
Thanks.

137
00:09:13,639 --> 00:09:14,399
Oh, by the way,

138
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,559
is that your car downstairs?

139
00:09:18,799 --> 00:09:19,440
Yeah, that's mine.

140
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:20,720
It's a mess.

141
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:21,879
It rained on my drive
from Su City,

142
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:24,080
got all splashed with mud.

143
00:09:26,559 --> 00:09:28,159
You came all the way from Su City?

144
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:29,840
You could've just told me

145
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,240
you were doing that for the game.

146
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:32,960
It's definitely not for the game.

147
00:09:33,759 --> 00:09:34,759
I wanted to see you anyway,

148
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,039
the livestream just gave me
an excuse to call.

149
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,080
There's something

150
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:44,720
I need to apologize for in person,

151
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:45,759
I couldn't live with myself if I didn't.

152
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,320
Give me one second,

153
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:51,399
I need to take care of something.

154
00:09:51,919 --> 00:09:52,360
Sure.

155
00:10:07,879 --> 00:10:08,519
Mr. Xu,
I'm so sorry.

156
00:10:09,879 --> 00:10:11,000
My phone died just now,

157
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:11,679
so I couldn't
check in with you.

158
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:13,759
Sorry.

159
00:10:16,519 --> 00:10:17,600
A friend just came over.

160
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,919
You weren't looking at Li Shican.

161
00:10:26,559 --> 00:10:28,120
You just saw him

162
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:29,639
and got reminded of that Xu guy again.

163
00:10:31,559 --> 00:10:34,159
Mr. Xu?

164
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:37,600
Hello.

165
00:10:38,919 --> 00:10:39,600
Sorry about that.

166
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,639
Don't check in with me.

167
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:44,679
Check in with the police instead.

168
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:46,639
Police?

169
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:50,679
He's your retained attorney?

170
00:10:52,039 --> 00:10:52,440
Yeah.

171
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:04,720
I need to take this.

172
00:11:07,879 --> 00:11:08,320
Hello?
[Shican,]

173
00:11:09,559 --> 00:11:10,720
[the cops just arrested me downstairs!]

174
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:11,679
[Come help me!]

175
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:21,399
Just a moment, you two.

176
00:11:21,879 --> 00:11:22,360
Thanks.

177
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:27,919
Let's wait over there.

178
00:11:32,399 --> 00:11:33,720
I'm so sorry.

179
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:35,120
I overreacted,

180
00:11:35,559 --> 00:11:37,080
and got you and your friend

181
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:37,960
dragged into this investigation.

182
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:38,879
My bad.

183
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:41,159
I should be the one apologizing.

184
00:11:41,399 --> 00:11:42,600
I didn't handle things properly

185
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,720
with Cen Sisi.

186
00:11:52,679 --> 00:11:54,039
She told me

187
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:55,799
you two were childhood friends?

188
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:57,879
I'm from Su City,

189
00:11:58,039 --> 00:11:58,919
she's from Hang City.

190
00:11:59,399 --> 00:12:00,240
How could we be childhood friends?

191
00:12:01,559 --> 00:12:02,360
Her dad moved to Su City

192
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:03,399
for business back then,

193
00:12:03,519 --> 00:12:05,000
so she transferred schools here.

194
00:12:05,399 --> 00:12:06,879
We were classmates for two years,

195
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,360
then went to the same college.

196
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:10,399
I guess that's why

197
00:12:10,399 --> 00:12:11,759
she thinks we're practically

198
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:13,600
childhood friends.

199
00:12:16,559 --> 00:12:17,559
She's had

200
00:12:17,559 --> 00:12:20,840
a crush on me for years.

201
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,200
I have a private Weibo account

202
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:25,320
that follows your Lily Vale account,

203
00:12:25,639 --> 00:12:27,600
she tracked you down through that,

204
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:30,519
and probably got the wrong idea.

205
00:12:37,399 --> 00:12:38,879
So how did you know I'm Lily Vale?

206
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:42,200
You asked me

207
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:43,240
to fix your computer back in college,

208
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:43,879
remember?

209
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:45,600
I saw your pen name

210
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:47,320
on a file name,

211
00:12:47,399 --> 00:12:49,080
remembered it,

212
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,240
and started following you.

213
00:12:53,399 --> 00:12:56,159
You've been hiding it well.

214
00:12:58,039 --> 00:13:00,000
I figured you creators

215
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,480
like to keep your online

216
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:02,879
and real lives separate,

217
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,639
otherwise it's like

218
00:13:04,639 --> 00:13:05,240
baring it all online.

219
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:07,240
But don't worry,

220
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,080
I don't stalk your account.

221
00:13:09,559 --> 00:13:10,960
That's why I only found out about this

222
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:11,879
after I came back to China.

223
00:13:12,159 --> 00:13:13,120
If I'd known earlier,

224
00:13:13,279 --> 00:13:13,960
I would've handled it right away.

225
00:13:17,080 --> 00:13:18,799
Someone's been deleting comments,

226
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:19,759
and leaking Cen Sisi's

227
00:13:19,759 --> 00:13:20,879
personal info.

228
00:13:21,559 --> 00:13:22,919
Was that your PR team?

229
00:13:24,399 --> 00:13:25,840
I told them to moderate the comments.

230
00:13:26,159 --> 00:13:28,159
I had no idea

231
00:13:28,679 --> 00:13:29,519
about the info leak.

232
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:33,799
Could it have been done by netizens?

233
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:37,039
Really?

234
00:13:39,279 --> 00:13:41,000
Either way, I got you into this mess,

235
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,279
and I'll clean it up.

236
00:13:42,679 --> 00:13:44,039
The hype's died down now.

237
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:45,639
Just focus on your lawsuit,

238
00:13:45,960 --> 00:13:48,039
leave the rest to me.

239
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:49,919
No need.

240
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:51,759
This isn't your fault anyway,

241
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:53,759
and you're swamped right now.

242
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,240
Don't waste your time on this.

243
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:57,320
I have a lawyer handling it for me.

244
00:14:01,559 --> 00:14:02,000
Oh, by the way,

245
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:03,600
I saw your

246
00:14:03,919 --> 00:14:05,600
lawyer's letter was signed

247
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:06,360
by Zhikun Law Firm.

248
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:07,879
Is Mr. Xu

249
00:14:09,159 --> 00:14:10,919
with Zhikun?

250
00:14:11,519 --> 00:14:12,080
Yeah.

251
00:14:12,519 --> 00:14:14,840
Is he reliable?

252
00:14:16,559 --> 00:14:17,080
Don't worry,

253
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:18,200
he's extremely professional
and experienced.

254
00:14:44,919 --> 00:14:45,879
Finally found you,

255
00:14:47,559 --> 00:14:48,200
Xu.

256
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:52,840
Looks like you've found her too.

257
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:10,840
Did you find

258
00:16:12,399 --> 00:16:13,559
your Hanazawa Rui?

259
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:34,120
[Mr. Xu,]

260
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:35,759
[I'm so sorry about today.]

261
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:36,960
[I made you worry for nothing.]

262
00:16:55,399 --> 00:16:56,200
[Mr. Xu,]

263
00:16:56,960 --> 00:16:58,080
[have you read the document?]

264
00:17:04,079 --> 00:17:05,680
He hasn't replied to a single one.

265
00:17:10,039 --> 00:17:10,799
Well, fair enough.

266
00:17:12,359 --> 00:17:13,960
Anyone would be upset

267
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:14,759
after being messed around like that,

268
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:15,880
especially when the police got called.

269
00:17:20,079 --> 00:17:20,720
Plus,

270
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:23,079
he's super busy to begin with.

271
00:17:26,279 --> 00:17:26,839
Or maybe

272
00:17:26,839 --> 00:17:28,119
he just hasn't seen them?

273
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:39,119
[Mr. Xu,]

274
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:41,279
[have you been busy these past two days?]

275
00:17:41,799 --> 00:17:42,759
[When will you have time]

276
00:17:42,759 --> 00:17:44,279
[to go over the case with me?]

277
00:17:57,319 --> 00:17:58,039
[In ten minutes.]

278
00:18:01,839 --> 00:18:02,799
[I'll go turn on my computer.]

279
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:05,400
[No need.]
[I'll be downstairs]

280
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:07,400
[at your place in ten minutes.]

281
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:31,680
No need to rush.

282
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:33,359
Sorry to keep you waiting,
Mr. Xu.

283
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:36,440
[All because of a silly mix-up,]

284
00:18:36,720 --> 00:18:37,680
[the great Mr. Xu]
[didn't reply to a single word from me]

285
00:18:38,599 --> 00:18:39,559
[for two days.]

286
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:41,920
[How dare I keep a big shot like you]

287
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,119
[waiting even a second longer?]

288
00:18:45,039 --> 00:18:46,839
Get in. We're going to the firm.

289
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:06,319
Well,

290
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:08,240
what are you doing near my place?

291
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:11,640
On the way from the airport to the firm.

292
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:15,359
[On the way from the airport to the firm?]

293
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:20,519
Thanks for picking me up.

294
00:19:29,279 --> 00:19:29,720
Hello?

295
00:19:30,599 --> 00:19:31,119
Ms. Zhang?

296
00:19:33,359 --> 00:19:34,279
Got it, I understand.

297
00:19:35,759 --> 00:19:36,200
Mr. Xu,

298
00:19:36,799 --> 00:19:38,279
Ms. Zhang ran into an emergency

299
00:19:38,279 --> 00:19:39,400
on a case at the construction site,

300
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:40,480
I have to head over there.

301
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:42,759
Then drop my luggage off

302
00:19:42,759 --> 00:19:43,880
at my apartment once you're done.

303
00:19:44,559 --> 00:19:44,960
Sure.

304
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:30,880
Should I get a taxi?

305
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:50,640
Or we can talk at my place?

306
00:20:51,359 --> 00:20:52,720
We can do it another time.

307
00:20:52,799 --> 00:20:53,640
I'll head back to the office first.

308
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:55,359
No, it's totally fine. This way please.

309
00:21:04,279 --> 00:21:05,000
Watch the steps.

310
00:21:13,759 --> 00:21:15,640
[He's only mad at you for two days,]

311
00:21:16,359 --> 00:21:17,920
[and look at you groveling like this.]

312
00:21:29,039 --> 00:21:29,799
[Oh shoot.]

313
00:21:31,359 --> 00:21:31,920
What's wrong?

314
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:34,920
Nothing.

315
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:37,039
Just a moment.

316
00:22:05,519 --> 00:22:06,400
Come on in.

317
00:22:20,519 --> 00:22:21,079
Sorry,

318
00:22:21,519 --> 00:22:22,759
I don't have men's slippers here.

319
00:22:23,319 --> 00:22:24,559
Just keep your shoes on.

320
00:22:41,599 --> 00:22:42,440
That's where I sat

321
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:43,599
for my videos earlier.

322
00:22:48,119 --> 00:22:49,240
A friend was over just now.

323
00:22:58,640 --> 00:22:59,319
Can I

324
00:22:59,519 --> 00:23:00,480
get you something to drink?

325
00:23:01,359 --> 00:23:02,119
Coffee's fine.

326
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:03,559
Is instant okay?

327
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:07,359
Alright, have a seat.

328
00:23:31,599 --> 00:23:32,480
[I was so focused on]

329
00:23:32,480 --> 00:23:33,720
[not wasting his trip,]

330
00:23:34,160 --> 00:23:34,920
[I forgot about the jet lag.]

331
00:23:35,799 --> 00:23:37,039
[I should've told him to go home.]

332
00:25:35,160 --> 00:25:35,680
Mr. Xu...

333
00:27:00,319 --> 00:27:01,079
Sorry,

334
00:27:01,519 --> 00:27:02,079
I fell asleep.

335
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:08,200
Hello?

336
00:27:10,680 --> 00:27:11,359
I just fell asleep.

337
00:27:13,519 --> 00:27:14,039
Haven't eaten yet.

338
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:16,599
Bye.

339
00:27:23,079 --> 00:27:24,839
You haven't eaten?

340
00:27:27,799 --> 00:27:29,440
Do you want to go get something first?

341
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:36,279
It's too hot out.

342
00:27:40,319 --> 00:27:41,440
Then should I order takeout?

343
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:45,079
You don't eat takeout.

344
00:27:51,039 --> 00:27:53,559
How about I make you something?

345
00:27:54,839 --> 00:27:55,799
I have food at home,

346
00:27:56,119 --> 00:27:58,359
we can make do with what we have.

347
00:28:02,039 --> 00:28:02,799
If it's not too much trouble.

348
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:04,839
It's no trouble at all.

349
00:28:05,279 --> 00:28:06,240
Come to the kitchen,
see if there's anything you want.

350
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:15,119
With the ingredients we have,

351
00:28:15,119 --> 00:28:17,000
I can make sandwiches or pasta.

352
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:18,440
Whatever you prefer.

353
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:22,480
This one.

354
00:28:25,559 --> 00:28:26,160
Your stomach

355
00:28:26,200 --> 00:28:27,480
hasn't fully adapted to Western food yet.

356
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:31,559
How do you want it cooked?

357
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:32,720
Fried.

358
00:28:34,079 --> 00:28:35,079
Go sit in the living room for a bit.

359
00:28:45,200 --> 00:28:47,880
[These aren't really good for frying.]

360
00:28:49,400 --> 00:28:50,599
[He probably wants]

361
00:28:50,599 --> 00:28:51,920
[Su-style lard rice cakes.]

362
00:29:09,599 --> 00:29:10,200
You know,

363
00:29:10,759 --> 00:29:11,440
I swapped it

364
00:29:11,440 --> 00:29:12,599
for Su-style lard rice cakes.

365
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:13,640
You probably

366
00:29:13,880 --> 00:29:14,920
don't get to eat these often abroad.

367
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:16,839
Thanks.

368
00:29:27,480 --> 00:29:28,319
How did you know

369
00:29:28,799 --> 00:29:29,599
I'm from Su City?

370
00:29:34,279 --> 00:29:35,240
I looked it up.

371
00:29:35,720 --> 00:29:37,079
There are news articles about you.

372
00:29:40,599 --> 00:29:41,759
Why did you look into me?

373
00:29:45,920 --> 00:29:46,759
Just

374
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:48,480
basic background

375
00:29:48,480 --> 00:29:49,319
on my attorney.

376
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:50,839
I also know

377
00:29:50,839 --> 00:29:52,559
Mr. Liu is from Hang City.

378
00:29:58,599 --> 00:29:59,119
Eat up

379
00:29:59,799 --> 00:30:00,759
while it's hot.

380
00:30:01,599 --> 00:30:02,039
Alright.

381
00:30:15,519 --> 00:30:16,759
[He's eating so politely.]

382
00:30:17,079 --> 00:30:18,640
[Does he like it or not?]

383
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:31,119
Want some?

384
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:33,160
I'm good.

385
00:30:34,079 --> 00:30:35,160
You eat up,

386
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:36,799
I'll go wash the dishes.

387
00:31:01,279 --> 00:31:02,400
[Well, his appetite sure isn't polite.]

388
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:04,599
[The frying turned out great today.]

389
00:31:06,480 --> 00:31:07,079
Are you full,
Mr. Xu?

390
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:15,240
I haven't read it yet.

391
00:31:17,359 --> 00:31:18,960
Have you been busy these days?

392
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:22,640
Haven't checked WeChat either.

393
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:30,240
[So he wasn't ignoring me on purpose.]

394
00:31:30,599 --> 00:31:31,440
[I knew it.]

395
00:31:31,440 --> 00:31:32,839
[He wouldn't be that petty.]

396
00:31:51,319 --> 00:31:52,559
Hello? What's up?

397
00:31:58,240 --> 00:31:59,200
The cat food is in the

398
00:31:59,200 --> 00:32:00,880
lower cabinet in the kitchen.

399
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:02,640
Yeah.

400
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:07,759
Just do whatever you think is best.

401
00:32:10,519 --> 00:32:12,359
First off, he has a cat.

402
00:32:12,559 --> 00:32:13,640
Second, he doesn't bathe

403
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:14,599
the cat himself.

404
00:32:14,599 --> 00:32:15,880
So

405
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:16,359
who does?

406
00:32:18,759 --> 00:32:19,519
Are you saying

407
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:22,319
there's someone else at his place?

408
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:25,160
He has a girlfriend?

409
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:28,279
He could just

410
00:32:28,279 --> 00:32:29,799
take the cat to a pet groomer,

411
00:32:29,799 --> 00:32:31,119
but what you're saying

412
00:32:31,119 --> 00:32:32,039
is definitely possible too.

413
00:32:39,559 --> 00:32:40,039
Ruan Yu,

414
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:42,880
I need to sleep for a bit.

415
00:32:54,559 --> 00:32:55,279
What,

416
00:32:57,119 --> 00:32:58,359
you're sleeping here?

417
00:32:59,599 --> 00:33:00,240
How about...

418
00:33:04,079 --> 00:33:04,680
Hey...

419
00:33:14,279 --> 00:33:16,079
He fell asleep that fast.

420
00:33:32,759 --> 00:33:34,440
Being a lawyer

421
00:33:34,440 --> 00:33:35,920
really is such an exhausting job.

422
00:35:42,840 --> 00:35:43,719
Mr. Xu,

423
00:35:44,559 --> 00:35:47,320
you've barely been in the office lately.

424
00:35:47,880 --> 00:35:49,800
It's been half a month

425
00:35:49,800 --> 00:35:51,039
since we last saw each other, right?

426
00:35:53,599 --> 00:35:54,800
Want a tea egg? My treat.

427
00:35:55,119 --> 00:35:55,599
No, thanks.

428
00:35:56,079 --> 00:35:57,119
I overate last night,

429
00:35:57,119 --> 00:35:58,079
still haven't digested it yet.

430
00:35:58,360 --> 00:35:59,039
What did you eat

431
00:35:59,199 --> 00:36:00,280
that's still sitting with you this long?

432
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:02,079
Fried lard rice cakes.

433
00:36:04,320 --> 00:36:05,599
How fancy of you.

434
00:36:05,599 --> 00:36:07,840
Naturally, it's a Su City specialty.

435
00:36:09,079 --> 00:36:10,760
Making fried rice cakes for yourself?

436
00:36:10,760 --> 00:36:11,480
Nice.

437
00:36:12,039 --> 00:36:13,320
Actually, I didn't make them.

438
00:36:21,320 --> 00:36:22,119
What's the story?

439
00:36:23,679 --> 00:36:24,599
Ruan Yu made them for me.

440
00:36:25,320 --> 00:36:25,719
Who?

441
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:27,000
Ruan Yu.

442
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:27,880
Why would she
make you fried rice cakes?

443
00:36:28,679 --> 00:36:29,400
What's going on between you two?

444
00:36:31,400 --> 00:36:32,760
Is it weird for a client to make

445
00:36:32,760 --> 00:36:34,440
fried rice cakes for their attorney?

446
00:36:34,679 --> 00:36:35,360
Are you kidding?
What client? What attorney?

447
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:36,760
Since when do clients make
fried rice cakes for their lawyers?

448
00:36:38,199 --> 00:36:39,800
Depends on the client,

449
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,000
and the attorney.
How so?

450
00:36:42,280 --> 00:36:43,239
Well, it can't be an attorney

451
00:36:43,239 --> 00:36:44,360
who's getting ahead of himself.

452
00:36:46,480 --> 00:36:49,079
Being likable is a gift, after all.

453
00:36:56,760 --> 00:36:57,519
Now grab your bag.
It's time for work.

454
00:36:59,519 --> 00:37:00,599
Did you just insult me?

455
00:37:01,280 --> 00:37:02,400
I swear you did, but I have no proof.

456
00:37:23,199 --> 00:37:24,440
[When are you gonna update?]

457
00:37:25,119 --> 00:37:26,320
[My comfort read,]

458
00:37:26,599 --> 00:37:27,800
[please come back soon.]

459
00:37:30,480 --> 00:37:32,239
What writer doesn't get writer's block?

460
00:37:33,400 --> 00:37:34,480
This time's different.

461
00:37:35,519 --> 00:37:37,440
The male lead's based on someone I know.

462
00:37:38,039 --> 00:37:38,679
How am I supposed

463
00:37:38,679 --> 00:37:40,119
to keep writing like nothing's wrong?

464
00:37:42,760 --> 00:37:44,320
[I'm convinced the author's innocent now.]

465
00:37:44,880 --> 00:37:47,000
[Just curious, is this book]

466
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:48,639
[really based on her real life?]

467
00:37:48,840 --> 00:37:49,920
[Same here.]

468
00:37:50,400 --> 00:37:51,239
[This whole thing blew up so bad.]

469
00:37:51,519 --> 00:37:52,480
[Does the real-life male lead]
[even know about it?]

470
00:38:04,320 --> 00:38:06,079
Anyone still working at this hour

471
00:38:06,639 --> 00:38:08,360
must be the elite of this city.

472
00:38:12,360 --> 00:38:13,079
[Mr. Xu,]
[I got your email.]

473
00:38:14,519 --> 00:38:15,960
[Thank you for working]

474
00:38:16,320 --> 00:38:16,920
[on my case so late.]

475
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:19,000
[Just killing time]
[while I get over my jet lag.]

476
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:23,920
[If you're still up,]

477
00:38:24,199 --> 00:38:25,280
[we can go over the case.]

478
00:38:26,559 --> 00:38:27,679
[Sure. Video call?]

479
00:38:28,360 --> 00:38:28,840
[Voice call is fine.]

480
00:38:47,519 --> 00:38:48,199
Sorry,

481
00:38:48,599 --> 00:38:49,760
hold on one second.

482
00:38:49,960 --> 00:38:50,960
I need to go grab a document downstairs.

483
00:38:52,280 --> 00:38:52,800
Alright.

484
00:39:03,039 --> 00:39:03,960
Mr. Xu?

485
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:05,960
I'm here.

486
00:39:09,079 --> 00:39:09,679
Well,

487
00:39:10,480 --> 00:39:12,480
is it raining where you are?

488
00:39:14,960 --> 00:39:15,599
It's pouring right now.

489
00:39:16,079 --> 00:39:16,880
Guess we're

490
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:18,760
under the same rain cloud then.

491
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:35,760
I'm back.

492
00:39:36,639 --> 00:39:37,119
Alright.

493
00:39:38,480 --> 00:39:39,320
Let's

494
00:39:40,239 --> 00:39:41,719
start with the third section.

495
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:44,079
This part is about

496
00:39:45,760 --> 00:39:48,360
the female lead, who's scared of thunder,

497
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:50,800
caught in an art museum by heavy rain.

498
00:39:51,800 --> 00:39:54,039
She overhears the male lead playing piano,

499
00:39:54,760 --> 00:39:56,119
and it calms her down.

500
00:39:57,639 --> 00:39:58,840
[This isn't in]

501
00:39:58,840 --> 00:39:59,360
[the other novel at all.]

502
00:40:00,079 --> 00:40:01,480
Do we need to bring this up?

503
00:40:02,320 --> 00:40:03,679
The descriptions of

504
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:04,960
the piano room in both novels

505
00:40:04,960 --> 00:40:06,199
are actually quite similar.

506
00:40:06,960 --> 00:40:07,800
All piano rooms
look pretty much the same.

507
00:40:09,119 --> 00:40:10,000
Did you forget?

508
00:40:12,719 --> 00:40:13,360
Forget what?

509
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,159
Did you forget

510
00:40:21,159 --> 00:40:22,519
to switch to WiFi?

511
00:40:23,039 --> 00:40:24,320
[Your connection seems bad,]

512
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:25,519
[I can barely hear you.]

513
00:40:32,320 --> 00:40:33,119
I already switched.

514
00:40:35,679 --> 00:40:36,320
It's good now,
I can hear you clearly.

515
00:40:37,840 --> 00:40:39,360
Alright, let's keep going.

516
00:40:41,119 --> 00:40:42,079
In the next section,

517
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:44,760
the female lead publicly turns down

518
00:40:44,760 --> 00:40:46,000
a male classmate who's been

519
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:46,599
harassing her,

520
00:40:47,039 --> 00:40:47,719
telling him to stop

521
00:40:47,719 --> 00:40:49,039
disturbing her studies.

522
00:40:49,760 --> 00:40:50,840
The male lead

523
00:40:50,840 --> 00:40:51,920
sees this,

524
00:40:52,079 --> 00:40:53,559
and he won't disrupt her studies either.

525
00:40:53,760 --> 00:40:54,440
So he never confesses

526
00:40:54,440 --> 00:40:55,719
his feelings to her.

527
00:40:56,599 --> 00:40:58,880
Right, I checked, The Poet

528
00:40:58,880 --> 00:40:59,800
hasn't written about
why the male lead

529
00:41:00,480 --> 00:41:01,719
never confessed yet.

530
00:41:02,360 --> 00:41:04,039
This part won't be called a trope copy?

531
00:41:04,519 --> 00:41:05,599
But this trope

532
00:41:05,960 --> 00:41:06,960
is a bit unreasonable.

533
00:41:09,159 --> 00:41:10,559
[Is my writing that unreasonable?]

534
00:41:12,239 --> 00:41:13,920
But the biggest worry for high schoolers

535
00:41:14,440 --> 00:41:15,360
is their studies.

536
00:41:16,559 --> 00:41:17,400
What other reason

537
00:41:18,199 --> 00:41:19,239
would the male lead have

538
00:41:19,239 --> 00:41:19,840
for not confessing?

539
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:24,719
Not every high schooler

540
00:41:25,760 --> 00:41:26,719
is that lucky.

541
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:33,360
I was being too absolute.

542
00:41:39,159 --> 00:41:40,559
Will this trope

543
00:41:41,360 --> 00:41:42,800
affect the lawsuit?

544
00:41:45,440 --> 00:41:46,119
It's fine,

545
00:41:46,440 --> 00:41:47,480
I'm just giving you a heads-up.

546
00:41:48,480 --> 00:41:49,199
You still need

547
00:41:49,360 --> 00:41:50,880
to keep updating your novel,

548
00:41:51,480 --> 00:41:52,880
so if you sort out your train of thought

549
00:41:53,079 --> 00:41:53,800
and resume updates soon,

550
00:41:54,320 --> 00:41:54,840
it'll help turn the public opinion

551
00:41:54,840 --> 00:41:56,239
around for the better.

552
00:41:58,320 --> 00:41:59,000
Yeah.

553
00:42:15,760 --> 00:42:16,360
The rain stopped.

554
00:42:37,400 --> 00:42:38,519
It's pouring so hard.

555
00:42:39,119 --> 00:42:39,760
I should've never come

556
00:42:39,760 --> 00:42:40,800
to feed the cats today.

557
00:43:03,280 --> 00:43:04,119
[Is that him?]

558
00:43:54,480 --> 00:43:55,159
[Xu Huaisong,]

559
00:43:56,079 --> 00:43:56,920
[your bright,]

560
00:43:56,920 --> 00:43:58,320
[untainted boyish charm]

561
00:43:59,119 --> 00:44:00,639
[cleared up every single]

562
00:44:01,199 --> 00:44:01,840
[rainy season]

563
00:44:02,920 --> 00:44:04,079
[of my youth.]

564
00:44:48,880 --> 00:44:49,559
Hello? Dad.

565
00:44:50,880 --> 00:44:52,079
Alright, I'm coming out now.

566
00:45:03,039 --> 00:45:05,480
The rain stopped here too.

567
00:45:06,840 --> 00:45:07,719
Let's keep going then.

568
00:45:09,960 --> 00:45:10,440
Alright.

569
00:45:57,960 --> 00:45:58,440
Ruan Yu?

570
00:46:38,239 --> 00:46:38,760
What's wrong?

571
00:46:39,760 --> 00:46:41,119
I'm so sorry,

572
00:46:41,800 --> 00:46:42,599
I accidentally fell asleep
last night.

573
00:46:45,239 --> 00:46:46,519
Why didn't you hang up?

574
00:46:47,559 --> 00:46:49,719
I must've fallen asleep too around then.

575
00:46:54,880 --> 00:46:55,280
Alright,

576
00:46:57,719 --> 00:46:58,840
I'll hang up then.

